comment: |-
  bun is a modern JavaScript/TypeScript runtime and package manager. It can be abused to run arbitrary scripts or install malicious packages, enabling code execution and persistence without requiring elevated privileges.
functions:
  file-write:
  - code: |-
      bun add malware
    contexts:
      sudo:
        comment: |-
          If run with elevated privileges, Bun can install packages system-wide, dropping malicious files globally.
      unprivileged:
        comment: |-
          Installs a malicious package into the project, enabling persistence and arbitrary file writes.
  inherit:
  - code: |-
      bun run --watch
    comment: |-
      The `--watch` flag spawns file watchers and external processes, which can be leveraged to execute arbitrary commands via inheritance.
    contexts:
      unprivileged:
    from: node
